+    "reality": "map-reduce.plan rejects in TWO cases, not one: (a) when more than one item carries inputs.mapReduce, and (b) when the single splitter's inputs.mapReduce is malformed. The 'only if' qualifier in the page is provably false — assertMapReduceConfig throws descriptive Errors for a non-object config, a missing/non-string map.executor, missing/non-object map.inputs, and the equivalents on reduce. The page even acknowledges this earlier ('map-reduce.plan calls assertMapReduceConfig … and throws a descriptive Error'), so the two claims internally contradict.",
