+    "reality": "In the source, each skipped descendant's S entry uses ITS OWN base parsed from the descendant's id, not the failed gate's base. With the page's binding of `base` carried over from the fix-item bullet, the formula `${base}~${next}` would map every skipped descendant `package` to `review~2` (the gate's base), but the implementation maps `package` to `package~2`. The page's formula should read `${parseAttempt(d).base}~${next}` to be literally correct; as written it conflates the gate's base with each descendant's base.",
